## SECTION 4 — AUDIT TRAIL: OPERATIONAL RISKS

The following risks are documented for the audit trail and must be addressed in the implementation roadmap:

| # | Risk | Mitigation Required |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Operational disruption from tool consolidation** — merging overlapping SaaS tools (Workato/Zapier, Cognism/Lusha, AWS entities) could interrupt live integrations and workflows | Phased migration plan required for each consolidation group; no simultaneous cutover; parallel-run period for critical tools |
| 2 | **Contract lock-in and early termination penalties** — terminating vendors mid-contract triggers penalty clauses; applies particularly to multi-year SaaS agreements (Adobe, Outreach, 6Sense, Uberflip) | All Terminate/Consolidate actions must be aligned to renewal windows; contract expiry dates must be confirmed before actioning |
| 3 | **Savings realisation delay due to migration costs** — consolidation projects incur one-time migration, data transfer, retraining, and integration costs that offset Year 1 savings | Net savings model required for all Tier 1 and Tier 2 consolidations; gross savings figures must not be reported without netting off transition costs |
| 4 | **Stakeholder resistance from business unit owners** — department heads (Sales, Engineering, Marketing, Product) may resist termination of tools embedded in their workflows | Executive sponsorship required; business unit sign-off process before action; change management and communication plan needed alongside each recommendation |

